Welcome to the Corporate Casket, a semiweekly series where bad businesses go to die. We will discuss any and everything from bad charities, terrible CEOs, and businesses that have a lot to hide. 

Dolce and Gabanna is one of the biggest fashion houses in the world. With dresses that cost more than a lot of peoples rent for an entire year, they claim their clothes, bags, and accessories are more than just fashion; their art. But, the company, and subsequently the owners of the brand seem to be skilled at more than just designing clothes. Theyre pretty good at stirring up some controversy and creating massive scandals. They dont seem to care though, as it seems they are pretty much uncancelable. Still, cant blame a pyramid for trying. Dont feed the monsters.
